President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Carla D. Hayden as the Librarian of Congress. If confirmed, Hayden would be the first woman and the first African American to hold the position. Hayden is currently the CEO of the Enoch Pratt Free Library in Baltimore and has dedicated her career to modernizing libraries. She has experience working in various library positions and was the President of the American Library Association from 2003 to 2004. Hayden has also received recognition for her outreach services, including an afterschool center for Baltimore teens. She holds a B.A. from Roosevelt University and an M.A. and Ph.D. from the Graduate Library School of the University of Chicago.